    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-08-20T20:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-08-20T20:45:00-05:00" n="370"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <head>370. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d370fn1"
                        >Source: Statement on suspension of nuclear testing. Confidential. 1 p.
                        NARA, <gloss target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59, Secretary’s Memoranda of
                        Conversation: Lot 64 D 199.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1958-08-20T21:45:00-04:00"
                            >August 20, 1958, 9:45 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d370-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d370-1"/>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="italic">United States</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>The Secretary</item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RGF_1">Reinhardt</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Mr. Greene</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="italic">United Kingdom</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_LJSB_1">Lloyd</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Sir William Hayter</item>
                            <item>Mr. A. R. Moore</item>
                            <item>Mr. Dennis Lasky</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Statement on Suspension of Nuclear Testing</hi>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>The Secretary showed Mr. <persName corresp="#p_LJSB_1">Lloyd</persName> the draft
                    of a statement proposed to be made by the President on suspension of nuclear
                    testing. In a lengthy discussion Mr. <persName corresp="#p_LJSB_1"
                        >Lloyd</persName> argued that unless there be established in the statement a
                    relationship between our readiness to suspend testing and Soviet willingness to
                    join in negotiations for an agreement to supervise suspension of testing, we
                    would give away to the Soviets <pb facs="1537" n="1432" type="typeset"
                        xml:id="pg_1432"/> without exacting any price an essential indeed
                    fundamental part of our position.</p>
                <p>As a result of this discussion, the Secretary agreed to insert at the beginning
                    of the fourth paragraph the phrase “If this is accepted in principle”, so as to
                    establish the link between the two parts of our statement.</p>
            </div>
